														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2104104">
									

<p>There were some grammar slip ups (&quot;there has been an accident&quot;) and parts of the syntax bugged me (&quot;a heavy piece of gauze&#8230; A heavy bandage&#8230;&quot; Using the word &quot;heavy&quot; twice in two back-to-back sentences reads a bit awkwardly) and the part where the father seems only to be mildly exasperated/counciling after his son tried to saw his own arm off kind of drew me out of the story (Yeah I know he screamed &quot;Jesus Christ&quot; but after that he didn't seem as concerned as a father would be in that situation&#8230; Like I don't think that he'd be muttering &quot;Oh buddy&#8230;&quot; and all that) but aside from these minor quibbles I enjoyed it enough to upvote.</p>

							</div>

										<div class="signature">
					<hr class="signature-separator"/>
					

<p>And if the whole world is crashing down&#8230; fall through space out of mind with me.</p>

				</div>
					
					
